style="text-align:center"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">PHILIP MORRIS INTERNATIONAL INC. (PMI) PRESENTS AT THE 2021 BARCLAYS </font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">GLOBAL CONSUMER STAPLES CONFERENCE&#59;</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">REAFFIRMS 2021 FULL-YEAR REPORTED DILUTED EPS FORECAST </font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">RANGE OF $5.76 TO $5.86,</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">REPRESENTING ADJUSTED DILUTED EPS OF $5.97 TO $6.07 AND</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">ORGANIC GROWTH OF AROUND 12% TO 14%&#59;</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:174%;text-decoration:underline">NOW EXPECTS TO BE TOWARD UPPER END OF FORECAST RANGE</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">NEW YORK, September 8, 2021 --</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">Philip Morris International Inc.&#8217;s (NYSE&#58; PM) Chief Financial Officer, Emmanuel Babeau, addresses investors today at the Barclays Global Consumer Staples Conference.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;margin-top:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">The presentation and Q&#38;A session will be conducted in a virtual format, beginning at approximately 8&#58;00 a.m. Eastern Time. A live video webcast of the entire PMI session will be available, in a listen-only mode, at </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%;text-decoration:underline">www.pmi.com&#47;2021barclays</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">. Presentation slides will be available on the same site.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">An archived copy of the webcast will be available at </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%;text-decoration:underline">www.pmi.com&#47;2021barclays</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%"> until 5&#58;00 p.m. Eastern Time on Thursday, October 7, 2021. The archived webcast can also be accessed on iOS or Android devices by downloading PMI&#8217;s free Investor Relations Mobile Application at </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%;text-decoration:underline">www.pmi.com&#47;irapp</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">&#8220;We remain on-track for an excellent performance in 2021, underpinned by better combustible volumes and continued strong demand for IQOS,&#8221; </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">said Jacek Olczak, Chief Executive Officer. </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">&#8220;We are today reaffirming our full-year EPS forecast and now expect to be toward the upper end of our 12% to 14% organic growth range.&#8221;</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">&#8220;While the increased impact of the global semiconductor shortage is currently limiting our ability to realize the full potential of IQOS, the underlying momentum of the brand is clear &#8211; as evidenced by the positive early results for IQOS ILUMA in Japan following the launch last month.&#8221;</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:12pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">2021 Full-Year Forecast</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;margin-top:12pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">PMI reaffirms its full-year reported diluted EPS forecast range of $5.76 to $5.86, reflecting a favorable currency impact, at prevailing exchange rates, of $0.18. On an organic basis, this forecast represents a projected increase of around 12% to 14% versus adjusted diluted EPS of $5.17 in 2020, as outlined in the table below.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;margin-top:12pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">The company now expects to be toward the upper end of the forecast range.</font></div><div style="height:61.61pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font previously).</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">This forecast the judgment in the two Qu&#233;bec Class Action lawsuits and the Companies&#8217; Creditors Arrangement Act (CCAA) protection granted to PMI's Canadian subsidiary, Rothmans, Benson &#38; Hedges, Inc. (RBH), any unusual events, any further intensification of the global shortage of semiconductors and the related impact on the supply of our electronic devices, and any COVID-19-related developments different from the assumptions set forth in the company's forecast.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">Factors described in the Forward-Looking and Cautionary Statements section of this release represent continuing risks to these projections.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:12pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Forward-Looking &#38; Cautionary Statements</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">This press release, the presentation and related discussion contain projections of future results and other forward-looking statements. excise tax increases and discriminatory tax structures&#59; increasing marketing and regulatory restrictions that could reduce our competitiveness, eliminate our ability to communicate with adult consumers, or ban certain of our products in certain markets or countries&#59; adverse changes in the cost, availability, and quality of tobacco and other agricultural products and raw materials, as well as components and materials for our electronic devices&#59; and the integrity of its information systems and effectiveness of its data privacy policies. PMI's future profitability may also be adversely affected should it be unsuccessful in its attempts to produce and commercialize reduced-risk products or if regulation or taxation do not differentiate between such products and cigarettes&#59; if it is unable to successfully introduce new products, promote brand equity, enter new markets or improve its margins through increased prices and productivity gains&#59; if it is unable to expand its brand portfolio internally or through acquisitions and the development of strategic business relationships&#59; or if it is unable to attract and retain the best global talent. Future results are also subject to the lower predictability of our reduced-risk product category's performance.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">In addition, PMI&#8217;s business risks also include risks and uncertainties related to PMI&#8217;s potential acquisitions of Fertin Pharma A&#47;S (&#8220;Fertin&#8221;) and Vectura Group plc (&#8220;Vectura&#8221;), including, amongst other things&#58; (1) the inability to consummate these acquisitions in a timely manner&#59; (2) the inability to complete these acquisitions due to the failure to satisfy certain conditions to complete the acquisitions, including any required regulatory approvals, as applicable&#59; (3) the failure of these acquisitions to close for any other reason&#59; (4) the possibility that the integration of the operations of Fertin and Vectura with those of PMI may be more difficult and&#47;or take longer than anticipated, and may not accelerate PMI&#8217;s desired entry into additional smoke-free and beyond nicotine platforms as quickly as anticipated&#59; (5) the possibility that the respective integrations of Fertin and Vectura into PMI may be more costly than anticipated and may have unanticipated adverse results relating to Fertin, Vectura or PMI&#8217;s existing businesses&#59; (6) the inability to gain access to differentiated proprietary technology and pharmaceutical development expertise as anticipated by these acquisitions&#59; (7) risks associated with third-party contracts containing consent and&#47;or other provisions that may be triggered by the proposed acquisitions&#59; (8) negative effects of the announcement or the consummation of the acquisitions on the market price of PMI&#8217;s common stock&#59; and (9) the ability of PMI to retain and hire key personnel of Fertin and Vectura.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">The COVID-19 pandemic has created significant societal and economic disruption, and resulted in closures of stores, factories and offices, and restrictions on manufacturing, distribution and travel, all of which will adversely impact our business, results of operations, cash flows and financial position during the continuation of the pandemic. Our business continuity plans and other safeguards may not be effective to mitigate the impact of the pandemic. Currently, significant risks include our diminished ability to convert adult smokers to our RRPs, significant volume declines in our duty-free business and certain other key markets, disruptions or delays in our manufacturing and supply chain, increased currency volatility, and delays in certain cost saving, transformation and restructuring initiatives. Our business could also be adversely impacted if key personnel or a significant number of employees or business partners become unavailable due to the COVID-19 outbreak. The significant adverse impact of COVID-19 on the economic or political conditions in markets in which we operate could result in changes to the preferences of our adult consumers </font></div><div style="height:61.61pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">3</font></div><div><font><br></font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:36pt;width:100%"><div><font><br></font></div></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">and lower demand for our products, particularly for our mid-price or premium-price brands. Continuation of the pandemic could disrupt our access to the credit markets or increase our borrowing costs. Governments may temporarily be unable to focus on the development of science-based regulatory frameworks for the development and commercialization of RRPs or on the enforcement or implementation of regulations that are significant to our business. In addition, messaging about the potential negative impacts of the use of our products on COVID-19 risks may lead to increasingly restrictive regulatory measures on the sale and use of our products, negatively impact demand for our products, the willingness of adult consumers to switch to our RRPs and our efforts to advocate for the development of science-based regulatory frameworks for the development and commercialization of RRPs.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">The impact of these risks also depends on factors beyond our knowledge or control, including the duration and severity of the pandemic, its recurrence in our key markets, actions taken to contain its spread and to mitigate its public health effects, and the ultimate economic consequences thereof.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">PMI is further subject to other risks detailed from time to time in its publicly filed documents, including the Form 10-Q for the quarter ended June 30, 2021. PMI cautions that the foregoing list of important factors is not a complete discussion of all potential risks and uncertainties. PMI does not undertake to update any forward-looking statement that it may make from time to time, except in the normal course of its public disclosure obligations.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:12pt;text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Philip Morris International&#58; Delivering a Smoke-Free Future</font></div><div style="text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">Philip Morris International (PMI) is leading a transformation in the tobacco industry to create a smoke-free future and ultimately replace cigarettes with smoke-free products to the benefit of adults who would otherwise continue to smoke, society, the company, its shareholders and its other stakeholders. PMI is a leading international tobacco company engaged in the manufacture and sale of cigarettes, as well as smoke-free products, associated electronic devices and accessories, and other nicotine-containing products in markets outside the U.S. In addition, PMI ships versions of its </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">IQOS</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%"> Platform 1 device and consumables to Altria Group, Inc. for sale under license in the U.S., where these products have received marketing authorizations from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) under the premarket tobacco product application (PMTA) pathway&#59; the FDA has also authorized the marketing of a version of </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">IQOS</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%"> and its consumables as a Modified Risk Tobacco Product (MRTP), finding that an exposure modification order for these products is appropriate to promote the public health. PMI is building a future on a new category of smoke-free products that, while not risk-free, are a much better choice than continuing to smoke. Through multidisciplinary capabilities in product development, state-of-the-art facilities and scientific substantiation, PMI aims to ensure that its smoke-free products meet adult consumer preferences and rigorous regulatory requirements. PMI's smoke-free product portfolio includes heat-not-burn and nicotine-containing vapor products. As of June 30, 2021, PMI's smoke-free products are available for sale in 67 markets in key cities or nationwide, and PMI estimates that approximately 14.7 million adults around the world have already switched to </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">IQOS</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%"> and stopped smoking. For more information, please visit </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%;text-decoration:underline">www.pmi.com</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%"> and </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%;text-decoration:underline">www.pmiscience.com</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">.</font></div><div style="height:61.61pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">4</font></div><div><font><br></font></div></div></div></body></html>

<DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">Forward-Looking and Cautionary Statements (COVID-19) &#8226; The COVID-19 pandemic has created significant societal and economic disruption, and resulted in closures of stores, factories and offices, and restrictions on manufacturing, distribution and travel, all of which will adversely impact our business, results of operations, cash flows and financial position during the continuation of the pandemic. Our business continuity plans and other safeguards may not be effective to mitigate the impact of the pandemic &#8226; Currently, significant risks include our diminished ability to convert adult smokers to our RRPs, significant volume declines in our duty-free business and certain other key markets, disruptions or delays in our manufacturing and supply chain, increased currency volatility, and delays in certain cost saving, transformation and restructuring initiatives. Our business could also be adversely impacted if key personnel or a significant number of employees or business partners become unavailable due to the COVID-19 outbreak. The significant adverse impact of COVID-19 on the economic or political conditions in markets in which we operate could result in changes to the preferences of our adult consumers and lower demand for our products, particularly for our mid-price or premium-price brands. Continuation of the pandemic could disrupt our access to the credit markets or increase our borrowing costs. Governments may temporarily be unable to focus on the development of science-based regulatory frameworks for the development and commercialization of RRPs or on the enforcement or implementation of regulations that are significant to our business. In addition, messaging about the potential negative impacts of the use of our products on COVID-19 risks may lead to increasingly restrictive regulatory measures on the sale and use of our products, negatively impact demand for our products, the willingness of adult consumers to switch to our RRPs and our efforts to advocate for the development of science-based regulatory frameworks for the development and commercialization of RRPs &#8226; The impact of these risks also depends on factors beyond our knowledge or control, including the duration and severity of the pandemic, its recurrence in our key markets, actions taken to contain its spread and to mitigate its public health effects, and the ultimate economic consequences thereof 3 On Track for Very Strong Q3 and FY Performance  &#8226; Strong outlook confirmed: &#8210; Continue to expect total volume growth for the year &#8210; Positive early results from ILUMA launch in Japan, surpassing prior launches at the same stage &#8210; Continued IQOS momentum; robust HTU growth in all key regions &#8210; Combustible volume trends better than expected  &#8226; Now expect to be toward upper end of forecast 2021 guidance range of $5.97-$6.07 in adjusted diluted EPS,  including Q3 assumption of $1.50-$1.55 &#8226; Strong demand and ongoing global semiconductor shortage leading to tighter IQOS device supply: &#8210; Some impact of reduced assortment &amp; availability on user acquisition in certain markets, such as Russia &#8210; H2 ILUMA launches; Japan live, most further H2 launches now planned for 2022 as we prioritize user acquisition    &#8210; 2021 HTU shipments could be toward lower end of 95-100bn range if shortages persist &#8226; Fertin, Vectura &amp; Otitopic acquisitions: complementary capabilities to support long-term growth ambitions  beyond nicotine &#8226; Launch of Business Transformation-linked Financing Framework 4 Source: PMI Financials or estimates  </FONT></DIV>

<DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">Glossary: General Terms  &#8226; &quot;PMI&quot; refers to Philip Morris International Inc. and its subsidiaries. Trademarks and service marks that are the registered property of, or  licensed by, the subsidiaries of PMI, are italicized &#8226; Until March 28, 2008, PMI was a wholly owned subsidiary of Altria Group, Inc. (&quot;Altria&quot;). Since that time the company has been independent and  is listed on the New York Stock Exchange (ticker symbol &quot;PM&quot;) &#8226; Comparisons are made to the same prior-year period unless otherwise stated &#8226; Unless otherwise stated, references to total industry, total market, PMI shipment volume and PMI market share performance reflect cigarettes  and heated tobacco units &#8226; References to total international market, defined as worldwide cigarette and heated tobacco unit volume excluding the U.S., total industry, total  market and market shares are PMI estimates for tax-paid products based on the latest available data from a number of internal and external  sources and may, in defined instances, exclude the People's Republic of China and/or PMI's duty free business &#8226; 2020 and 2021 estimates for total industry volume and market share in certain geographies reflect limitations on the availability and accuracy  of industry data during pandemic-related restrictions &#8226; &quot;OTP&quot; is defined as &quot;other tobacco products,&quot; primarily roll-your-own and make-your-own cigarettes, pipe tobacco, cigars and cigarillos, and  does not include reduced-risk products &#8226; &quot;Combustible products&quot; is the term PMI uses to refer to cigarettes and OTP, combined &#8226; In-market sales, or &quot;IMS,&quot; is defined as sales to the retail channel, depending on the market and distribution model &#8226; &quot;Total shipment volume&quot; is defined as the combined total of cigarette shipment volume and heated tobacco unit shipment volume &#8226; &quot;RBH&quot; refers to PMI&#8217;s Canadian subsidiary, Rothmans, Benson &amp; Hedges Inc. &#8226; The Companies&#8217; Creditors Arrangement Act (CCAA) is a Canadian federal law that permits a Canadian business to restructure its affairs while  carrying on its business in the ordinary course 7 Glossary: General Terms (cont.) &#8226; &quot;EU&quot; is defined as the European Union Region &#8226; &quot;EE&quot; is defined as the Eastern Europe Region &#8226; &quot;ME&amp;A&quot; is defined as the Middle East &amp; Africa Region and includes PMI's duty free business  &#8226; &quot;S&amp;SA&quot; is defined as the South &amp; Southeast Asia Region  &#8226; &quot;EA&amp;A&quot; is defined as the East Asia &amp; Australia Region  &#8226; &quot;LA&amp;C&quot; is defined as the Latin America &amp; Canada Region. In July 2021, the Latin America &amp; Canada operating segment was renamed as the  Americas operating segment &#8226; Following the deconsolidation of PMI's Canadian subsidiary, Rothmans, Benson &amp; Hedges, Inc. (RBH), PMI will continue to report the volume of  brands sold by RBH for which other PMI subsidiaries are the trademark owner.  These include HEETS, Next, Philip Morris and Rooftop &#8226; From time to time, PMI&#8217;s shipment volumes are subject to the impact of distributor inventory movements, and estimated total industry/market  volumes are subject to the impact of inventory movements in various trade channels that include estimated trade inventory movements of  PMI&#8217;s competitors arising from market-specific factors that significantly distort reported volume disclosures. Such factors may include changes  to the manufacturing supply chain, shipment methods, consumer demand, timing of excise tax increases or other influences that may affect the  timing of sales to customers. In such instances, in addition to reviewing PMI shipment volumes and certain estimated total industry/market  volumes on a reported basis, management reviews these measures on an adjusted basis that excludes the impact of distributor and/or estimated  trade inventory movements. Management also believes that disclosing PMI shipment volumes and estimated total industry/market volumes in  such circumstances on a basis that excludes the impact of distributor and/or estimated trade inventory movements, such as on an IMS basis,  improves the comparability of performance and trends for these measures over different reporting periods &#8226; &quot;ESG&quot; stands for environmental, social, and governance &#8226; &quot;Illicit trade&quot; refers to domestic non-tax paid products &#8226; &quot;OECD&quot; is defined as Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development  &#8226; &quot;SoM&quot; stands for share of market 8 </FONT></DIV>
<P><HR noshade><P>
<DIV style="page-break-before:always;">&nbsp;</DIV>
</DIV>
<!-- a2021-09x8xbarclaysxslid005.jpg -->
<DIV style="padding-top:2em;">
<IMG src="a2021-09x8xbarclaysxslid005.jpg" title="slide5" width="965" height="1365">
<DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">Glossary: Financial Terms  &#8226; Net revenues related to combustible products refer to the operating revenues generated from the sale of these products, including shipping and handling charges billed to customers, net of sales and promotion incentives, and excise taxes. PMI recognizes revenue when control is  transferred to the customer, typically either upon shipment or delivery of goods &#8226; Net revenues related to RRPs represent the sale of heated tobacco units, heat-not-burn devices and related accessories, and other nicotine- containing products, primarily e-vapor products, including shipping and handling charges billed to customers, net of sales and promotion  incentives, and excise taxes. PMI recognizes revenue when control is transferred to the customer, typically either upon shipment or delivery  of goods  &#8226; Adjusted net revenues exclude the impact related to the Saudi Arabia customs assessments &#8226; &quot;SG&amp;A&quot; stands for selling, general &amp; administrative &#8226; &quot;Adjusted Operating Income (OI) Margin&quot; is calculated as adjusted OI, divided by adjusted net revenues  &#8226; &quot;Net debt&quot; is defined as total debt, less cash and cash equivalents &#8226; Growth rates presented on an organic basis for consolidated financial results reflect currency-neutral underlying results  &#8226; Management reviews net revenues, OI, OI margins, operating cash flow and earnings per share, or &quot;EPS,&quot; on an adjusted basis, which may  exclude the impact of currency and other items such as acquisitions, asset impairment and exit costs, tax items and other special items.  Organic growth rates reflect the way management views underlying performance for these measures. PMI believes that such measures,  including pro forma measures, will provide useful insight into underlying business trends and results. &#8226; &quot;Fair value adjustment for equity security investments&quot; reflects the adjustment resulting from share price movements in passive  investments for publicly traded entities that are not controlled or influenced by PMI. Under U.S. GAAP, such adjustments are required, since  January 1, 2018, to be reflected directly in the income statement 9 Glossary: Reduced-Risk Products &#8226; &quot;Reduced-risk products,&quot; or &quot;RRPs,&quot; is the term PMI uses to refer to products that present, are likely to present, or have the potential to  present less risk of harm to smokers who switch to these products versus continuing smoking. PMI has a range of RRPs in various stages of  development, scientific assessment and commercialization. PMI RRPs are smoke-free products that produce an aerosol that contains far lower quantities of harmful and potentially harmful constituents than found in cigarette smoke &#8226; &quot;Aerosol&quot; refers to a gaseous suspension of fine solid particles and/or liquid droplets &#8226; &quot;Combustion&quot; is the process of burning a substance in oxygen, producing heat and often light &#8226; &quot;Smoke&quot; is a visible suspension of solid particles, liquid droplets and gases in air, emitted when a material burns &#8226; &quot;Heated tobacco units,&quot; or &quot;HTUs,&quot; is the term PMI uses to refer to heated tobacco consumables, which for PMI include the company's  HEETS, HEETS Creations, HEETS Dimensions, HEETS Marlboro and HEETS FROM MARLBORO (defined collectively as HEETS), Marlboro  Dimensions, Marlboro HeatSticks and Parliament HeatSticks, as well as the KT&amp;G-licensed brand, Fiit and Miix (outside of Korea) &#8226; The IQOS heat-not-burn device is a precisely controlled heating device into which a specially designed and proprietary tobacco unit is  inserted and heated to generate an aerosol &#8226; &quot;PMI heat-not-burn products&quot; include licensed KT&amp;G heat-not-burn products &#8226; &quot;PMI HTUs&quot; include licensed KT&amp;G HTUs &#8226; HTU &quot;offtake volume&quot; represents the estimated retail offtake of HTUs based on a selection of sales channels that vary by market, but notably include retail points of sale and e-commerce platforms &#8226; HTU &quot;offtake share&quot; represents the estimated retail offtake volume of HTUs divided by the sum of estimated total offtake volume for  cigarettes and HTUs  &#8226; Market share for HTUs is defined as the total sales volume for HTUs as a percentage of the total estimated sales volume for cigarettes and  HTUs &#8226; &quot;Total IQOS users&quot; is defined as the estimated number of Legal Age (minimum 18 years) users of PMI heat-not-burn products for which  PMI HTUs represented at least 5% of their daily tobacco consumption over the past seven days. Note: as of December 2020, PMI heat- not-burn products and HTUs include licensed KT&amp;G heat-not-burn products and HTUs, respectively 10 </FONT></DIV>
<P><HR noshade><P>
<DIV style="page-break-before:always;">&nbsp;</DIV>
</DIV>
<!-- a2021-09x8xbarclaysxslid006.jpg -->
<DIV style="padding-top:2em;">
<IMG src="a2021-09x8xbarclaysxslid006.jpg" title="slide6" width="965" height="1365">
<DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">Glossary: Reduced-Risk Products (cont.) &#8226; The estimated number of adults who have &quot;switched to IQOS and stopped smoking&quot; reflects:&#9148; for markets where there are no heat-not-burn products other than PMI heat-not-burn products: daily individual consumption of PMI HTUs represents  the totality of their daily tobacco consumption in the past seven days&#9148; for markets where PMI heat-not-burn products are among other heat-not-burn products: daily individual consumption of HTUs represents the totality  of their daily tobacco consumption in the past seven days, of which at least 70% is PMI HTUs Note: as of December 2020, PMI heat-not-burn products and HTUs include licensed KT&amp;G heat-not-burn products and HTUs, respectively  &#8226; &quot;FDA&quot; stands for the U.S. Food &amp; Drug Administration  &#8226; &quot;MRTP&quot; stands for Modified Risk Tobacco Product, the term used by the U.S. FDA to refer to RRPs &#8226; &quot;MRTP application&quot; stands for Modified Risk Tobacco Product application under section 911 of the FD&amp;C Act &#8226; &quot;PMTA&quot; stands for Premarket Tobacco Application under section 910 of the FD&amp;C Act &#8226; &quot;Acquisition&quot; refers to our efforts to switch LAS from smoking cigarettes to RRPs or to switch LAU from competing smoke-free products to  PMI&#8217;s RRPs &#8226; &quot;Retention&quot; refers to our efforts to deter LAU from going back to smoking cigarettes or from choosing a competing smoke-free product instead  of a PMI RRP 11 Glossary: IQOS in the United States &#8226; On April 30, 2019, the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) announced that the marketing of a version of PMI's Platform 1 product,  namely, IQOS 2.4, together with its heated tobacco units (the term PMI uses to refer to heated tobacco consumables), is appropriate for the  protection of public health and authorized it for sale in the U.S. The FDA&#8217;s decision followed its comprehensive assessment of PMI&#8217;s  premarket tobacco product applications (PMTAs) submitted to the Agency in 2017 &#8226; In the third quarter of 2019, PMI brought IQOS 2.4 and three variants of its heated tobacco units to the U.S. through its license with Altria Group, Inc., whose subsidiary, Philip Morris USA Inc., is responsible for marketing the product and complying with the provisions set forth  in the FDA's marketing orders &#8226; On July 7, 2020, the FDA authorized the marketing of a version of PMI's Platform 1 product, namely, IQOS 2.4, together with its heated  tobacco units, as a Modified Risk Tobacco Product (MRTP). In doing so, the agency found that an IQOS exposure modification order is  appropriate to promote the public health. The decision followed a review of the extensive scientific evidence package PMI submitted to the  FDA in December 2016 to support its MRTP applications &#8226; On December 7, 2020, the FDA confirmed that the marketing of a version of PMI's Platform 1 product, namely, IQOS 3, is appropriate for  the protection of public health and authorized it for sale in the U.S. The FDA&#8217;s decision followed an assessment of a PMI's PMTA filed with  the agency in March 2020 &#8226; Shipment volume of heated tobacco units to the U.S. is included in the heated tobacco unit shipment volume of the Latin America &amp; Canada  segment. Revenues from shipments of Platform 1 devices, heated tobacco units and accessories to Altria Group, Inc. for sale under license  in the U.S. are included in Net Revenues of the Latin America &amp; Canada segment 12 </FONT></DIV>
<P><HR noshade><P>
<DIV style="page-break-before:always;">&nbsp;</DIV>
</DIV>

var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);

if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}
